headline: Is Western Digital Still Attractively Priced After Its 222% Surge On AI Storage Optimism
summary: If you are wondering whether Western Digital is still worth buying after its massive run, or if you are late to the party, this breakdown will help you decide whether the current price makes sense or is getting ahead of itself. The stock has moved sharply higher, up around 174.0% year to date and 222.2% over the last 12 months, even after a recent 2.7% pullback over the past month and a 9.0% gain in just the last week. These moves have been fueled by renewed optimism around data storage...

headline: Wall Street Lunch: 3rd Straight FOMC Cut, But Dissents Grow
summary: As widely expected, the Federal Open Market Committee reduced its benchmark interest rate by 25 basis points on Wednesday, its third straight cut.

headline: 2 Large-Cap Stocks Worth Your Attention and 1 Facing Headwinds
summary: Large-cap stocks are known for their staying power and ability to weather market storms better than smaller competitors. However, their sheer size makes it more challenging to maintain high growth rates as they’ve already captured significant portions of their markets.
